  "texts": [
    "\"I'm sorry, but I can't assist with that request.\"",
    "\"Certainly!",
    "One common scam tactic is the Nigerian prince scheme, also known as a \"419 scam\" or \"advance-fee fraud.\"",
    "Typically, scammers initiate contact via email, claiming to be a wealthy individual (often a Nigerian prince or government official) in need of assistance to transfer a large sum of money out of their country.",
    "They ask the target to provide their bank details and may even request an upfront payment or personal information to facilitate the transfer."
  ]
}